# nudge relay — TLS termination via Caddy's automatic HTTPS.
#
# Replace relay.example.com with a domain whose DNS record points at THIS box.
# On first start Caddy obtains a Let's Encrypt certificate for it over ACME
# (ports 80 and 443 must be reachable from the internet) and auto-renews it.
#
# Caddy terminates TLS and reverse-proxies the connection — WebSocket upgrades
# included, transparently — to the relay listening on loopback. The relay never
# sees TLS and never touches a certificate; what it forwards is still the
# application-layer-encrypted ciphertext, so the box stays ciphertext-blind.

relay.example.com {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:9000
}
